      <!-- Origin -->
      <div class="illuminated-box">
        <div class="char-section">
          <h3 class="t-en">From Stygia</h3>
          <h3 class="t-id">Dari Stygia</h3>

          <p class="t-en">
            Sogong Wahyudi is a tiefling. He is also, or was until recently, a fisherman.
            These two facts do not often appear in the same accounting, and yet here we are.
          </p>
          <p class="t-id">
            Sogong Wahyudi adalah seorang tiefling. Dan sebelum jadi Oathbreaker Paladin,
            ia adalah seorang pemancing. Dua fakta yang biasanya tidak muncul dalam satu napas,
            tapi begitulah adanya.
          </p>

          <p class="t-en" style="margin-top:0.8rem;">
            He comes from Stygia, the fifth layer of the Nine Hells of Baator, where he spent
            his days fishing the River Styx. This is not a figure of speech. He cast his line
            into the river that unmakes memory, pulled things out of it, and what he pulled was,
            without exception, fish. The same fish, every time. He noted this. He continued fishing.
            Eventually he arrived at a conclusion consistent with everything the party has since
            learned about him: he climbed.
          </p>
          <p class="t-id" style="margin-top:0.8rem;">
            Ia berasal dari Stygia, lapisan kelima Nine Hells of Baator. Di sanalah ia menghabiskan
            hari-harinya memancing di sepanjang Sungai Styx. Bukan kiasan. Ia melempar kail ke sungai
            yang menghapus ingatan, dan apa yang ia tangkap, selalu, adalah ikan. Ikan yang sama terus-menerus.
            Bosan dengan tangkapannya yang itu-itu saja, Sogong naik dari satu lapisan Neraka ke lapisan
            berikutnya, berharap dapat menangkap jenis ikan yang berbeda.
          </p>

          <p class="t-en" style="margin-top:0.8rem;">
            One layer at a time, upward through the architecture of the Hells. Not for power or contract
            or any of the usual reasons. He was bored with his fish and hoped the next layer might have
            different ones. They did not. Every layer of the Nine Hells offered the same catch dressed
            in new scenery. He kept climbing. The fish question was not resolved.
          </p>
          <p class="t-id" style="margin-top:0.8rem;">
            Namun di mana pun ia melempar kailnya, ikannya tetap sama. Ia terus naik.
            Masalah ikan tidak terselesaikan.
          </p>

          <p class="t-en" style="margin-top:0.8rem;">
            He reached Avernus, the first layer and the worst stop on the itinerary. Avernus is the
            main theater of the Blood War: the eternal war between the devils of Baator and the demons
            of the Abyss, running without resolution since before anyone in this party was born.
            Sogong was not there for the Blood War. The Blood War did not care. He was conscripted
            into the devil faction's infantry at a rank low enough that the hierarchy does not bother
            giving it a name. He served. The fish were not mentioned again.
          </p>
          <p class="t-id" style="margin-top:0.8rem;">
            Perjalanannya berakhir di Avernus, lapisan pertama Nine Hells, yang menjadi medan utama
            Blood War: perang abadi antara devil dari Baator dan demon dari Abyss yang sudah berjalan
            tanpa henti atau penyelesaian sejak sebelum siapa pun dalam rombongan ini lahir.
            Sogong tidak datang untuk Blood War. Blood War tidak peduli dengan perbedaan itu.
            Ia direkrut paksa ke infanteri faksi devil di pangkat yang hierarki devil tidak repot-repot
            memberi nama. Ia bertugas. Urusan ikan tidak lagi disebut-sebut.
          </p>

          <p class="t-en" style="margin-top:0.8rem;">
            In one of the major engagements on the Avernus plains, a nautiloid appeared in the sky.
            Sogong looked at it. He looked at the war he was standing in. He jumped.
          </p>
          <p class="t-id" style="margin-top:0.8rem;">
            Dalam salah satu pertempuran besar di dataran Avernus, sebuah nautiloid muncul menembus langit.
            Sogong memandangnya. Ia memandang perang tempat ia berdiri. Ia melompat.
          </p>

          <p class="t-en" style="margin-top:0.8rem;">
            He caught one of the tentacles on the way up. He climbed. The illithid's psionic influence
            introduced itself somewhere between the grip and the deck as a headache, and he lost
            consciousness before reaching the top. He woke up in chains, surrounded by people he had
            never met, with a tadpole in his head and no fish. This is, by any reasonable measure,
            the most interesting thing that had happened to him in years.
          </p>
          <p class="t-id" style="margin-top:0.8rem;">
            Ia berhasil memegang salah satu tentakel kapal. Ia memanjat. Di tengah upayanya, ia merasakan
            sakit kepala yang kuat, pertanda pengaruh psionik illithid. Meski begitu, ia berhasil naik
            ke dalam kapal sebelum akhirnya kehilangan kesadaran.
            Ia terbangun dalam belenggu, dikelilingi orang-orang asing, dengan berudu di kepalanya
            dan tanpa ikan. Ini, dengan ukuran apa pun yang wajar, adalah hal paling menarik
            yang terjadi padanya dalam bertahun-tahun.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- First Impression -->
      <div class="char-section">
        <h3 class="t-en">First Impression</h3>
        <h3 class="t-id">Kesan Pertama</h3>
        <p class="t-en">
          There is something clarifying about a man who announces his nature rather than
          waiting for you to discover it. Sogong said it plainly, without theater, in what
          was perhaps the second conversation any member of this party had with him:
          he is, by his own accounting, an evil person. He did not elaborate. He did not
          invite follow-up questions. He offered the information the way someone might
          mention the weather: relevant, apparently true, and not open to debate.
        </p>
        <p class="t-id">
          Ada sesuatu yang melegakan dari orang yang langsung bilang siapa dia, daripada
          menunggu kamu menemukan sendiri. Sogong mengatakannya dengan blak-blakan, tanpa basa-basi,
          di salah satu percakapan awalnya dengan rombongan: ia, kata dia sendiri, adalah orang jahat.
          Ia tidak menguraikan. Tidak mengundang pertanyaan lanjutan. Ia menawarkan informasi itu
          seperti orang menyebut cuaca: relevan, kelihatannya benar, dan tidak perlu diperdebatkan.
        </p>
        <p class="t-en" style="margin-top:0.8rem;">
          He is also, without question, the largest member of this company. The party has
          concluded that these two facts are probably related, though no one has asked directly how.
        </p>
        <p class="t-id" style="margin-top:0.8rem;">
          Ia juga, tanpa keraguan, anggota terbesar dari rombongan ini. Rombongan sudah sampai
          pada kesimpulan bahwa kedua fakta ini mungkin ada hubungannya, tapi tidak ada yang
          bertanya langsung bagaimana caranya.
        </p>
      </div>

      <hr class="divider" />

      <!-- The Shield That Remains -->
      <div class="char-section">
        <h3 class="t-en">The Shield That Remains</h3>
        <h3 class="t-id">Perisai yang Tersisa</h3>
        <p class="t-en">And yet.</p>
        <p class="t-id">Tapi.</p>
        <p class="t-en" style="margin-top:0.8rem;">
          When a companion is in danger, Sogong does not calculate. The shield comes up.
          The Sanctuary goes out. It is not a policy; it is a reflex, and it is a paladin's
          reflex specifically: the one that persists after everything else about an oath has
          been discarded, broken, or simply grown too heavy to carry. He moves to cover
          his companions with the automatic certainty of someone who was built for exactly
          this and has not stopped being built for it, regardless of what he tells people about himself.
        </p>
        <p class="t-id" style="margin-top:0.8rem;">
          Ketika seorang kawan dalam bahaya, Sogong tidak berhitung. Perisai naik. Sanctuary keluar.
          Ini bukan kebijakan, ini refleks. Refleks seorang paladin yang bertahan bahkan setelah
          segalanya tentang sumpah itu sudah dibuang, dilanggar, atau sekadar jadi terlalu berat
          untuk dibawa. Ia bergerak melindungi kawannya dengan kepastian otomatis seseorang yang
          memang diciptakan untuk ini, terlepas dari apa yang ia katakan tentang dirinya sendiri.
        </p>
        <p class="t-en" style="margin-top:0.8rem;">
          The party has noticed. No one has said anything directly. Beneath the bulk,
          the glower, and the self-assessment, something in Sogong Wahyudi is still standing guard.
          Whether he knows it, and whether he would admit it if he did, are two questions
          with answers he has not volunteered.
        </p>
        <p class="t-id" style="margin-top:0.8rem;">
          Rombongan sudah memperhatikan. Tidak ada yang bilang apa-apa secara langsung.
          Di balik tubuh besar, tatapan berat, dan pengakuan diri itu, ada sesuatu dalam diri
          Sogong Wahyudi yang masih berjaga. Apakah ia sadar, dan apakah ia mau mengakuinya
          kalau memang sadar, adalah dua pertanyaan yang belum ia jawab.
        </p>
      </div>

      <!-- Anaik's Gamble -->
      <div class="char-section">
        <h3 class="t-en">Anaik's Gamble</h3>
        <h3 class="t-id">Taruhan Anaik</h3>
        <p class="t-en">
          Anaik recruited him. This is worth examining, because Anaik's recruitment method
          consisted primarily of noticing that Sogong is very large and appears structurally
          resistant to a significant amount of incoming damage, and concluding that this was
          reason enough to bring him along. It was a purely pragmatic assessment, conducted
          with no particular interest in personality, alignment, or stated self-identification
          as an evil person. Anaik has never expressed regret about this.
          Sogong has never expressed anything about it at all.
        </p>
        <p class="t-id">
          Anaik yang merekrutnya. Ini menarik untuk ditelaah, karena metode rekrutmen Anaik
          pada dasarnya cuma: melihat bahwa Sogong sangat besar dan tampaknya tahan terhadap
          banyak kerusakan, lalu menyimpulkan bahwa itu alasan yang cukup untuk dibawa serta.
          Penilaian murni pragmatis, tanpa minat khusus pada kepribadian, keselarasan, atau fakta
          bahwa orang ini mengaku jahat. Anaik tidak pernah menyesal. Sogong tidak pernah
          berkomentar apa pun tentangnya.
        </p>
        <p class="t-en" style="margin-top:0.8rem;">
          What Anaik calculated: a body that could absorb what the rest of the party could not.
          What the party received: that, and something else they have not yet found the right word for.
        </p>
        <p class="t-id" style="margin-top:0.8rem;">
          Yang Anaik hitung: tubuh yang bisa menyerap apa yang tidak bisa diserap sisanya.
          Yang rombongan dapat: itu, dan sesuatu yang lain yang belum ada kata tepatnya.
        </p>
      </div>

      <hr class="divider" />

      <!-- The Unknown Ledger -->
      <div class="char-section">
        <h3 class="t-en">The Unknown Ledger</h3>
        <h3 class="t-id">Catatan yang Belum Terbaca</h3>
        <p class="t-en">
          His goals are his own. Sogong Wahyudi does not discuss his past with any apparent
          willingness. He does not explain his choices, his silences, or his continued presence
          in a company he joined under entirely unclear terms.
        </p>
        <p class="t-id">
          Tujuannya adalah miliknya sendiri. Sogong Wahyudi tidak membahas masa lalunya dengan
          kesediaan yang terlihat. Ia tidak menjelaskan pilihan-pilihannya, kediaman-keheningannya,
          atau kenapa ia masih ada di sini, di rombongan yang ia masuki dengan syarat yang sama
          sekali tidak jelas.
        </p>
        <p class="t-en" style="margin-top:0.8rem;">
          What motivates him? The evil-person explanation covers the surface and nothing beneath it.
          There is something underneath: there always is, with a man who climbed out of Hell one layer
          at a time, looking for different fish, and ended up here. What is not uncertain is this:
          when the moment comes, he will be standing in front of them.
        </p>
        <p class="t-id" style="margin-top:0.8rem;">
          Apa yang memotivasinya? Penjelasan "orang jahat" cuma menyentuh permukaannya.
          Ada sesuatu di bawah itu. Selalu ada, untuk orang yang memanjat keluar dari Neraka
          satu lapisan demi satu lapisan hanya karena bosan dengan ikannya, dan berakhir di sini.
          Yang pasti cuma satu: ketika momennya tiba, ia akan berdiri di depan mereka.
        </p>
      </div>

